p.-text
  | Buttons are used to trigger actions in forms, modals, and more.

h3 Button tags
p.-text
  | To render a button, use the tag <code>&lt;chi-button&gt;</code>.
  | The <code>&lt;chi-button&gt;</code> emits a custom event that you can listen to, the event name is <code>chiClick</code>
.example.-mb--3
  .-p--3.-d--flex
    each type in ['Button', 'Link', 'Input', 'Submit', 'Reset']
      div.-pr--2
        chi-button()= type
  :code(lang='html')
    <chi-button>Button</chi-button>
    <chi-button>Link</chi-button>
    <chi-button>Input</chi-button>
    <chi-button>Submit</chi-button>
    <chi-button>Reset</chi-button>

h3 Examples

h4 Base
p.-text
  | Chi includes a wide variety of predefined button colors. For light backgrounds set <code>color</code> attribute value to <code>primary</code> or <code>dark</code>.
  | For dark backgrounds, please limit usage to <code>secondary</code> or <code>light</code>
.example.-mb--3
  .a-grid.-noGutter
    .a-col.-w--12.-w-md--6
      .-p--3.-d--flex(style="justify-content: center;")
        each type, val in {Base:'', Primary:'primary', Dark:'dark'}
          div.-pr--2
            chi-button(color=type)= val
    .a-col.-w--12.-w-md--6
      .-p--3.-bg--black.-d--flex(style="justify-content: center;")
        each type, val in {Secondary:'secondary', Light:'light'}
          div.-pr--2
            chi-button(color=type)= val
  :code(lang='html')
    <!-- For light backgrounds -->
    <chi-button>Base</chi-button>
    <chi-button color='primary'>Primary</chi-button>
    <chi-button color='dark'>Dark</chi-button>

    <!-- For dark backgrounds -->
    <chi-button color='secondary'>Secondary</chi-button>
    <chi-button color='light'>Light</chi-button>


h4 Outline
p.-text
  | To remove a buttons solid background and keep it's colored border, apply the attribute
  | <code>outline</code> on the <code>&lt;chi-button&gt;</code> tag.
.example.-mb--3
  .a-grid.-noGutter
    .a-col.-w--12.-w-md--6
      .-p--3.-d--flex(style="justify-content: center;")
        each type, val in {Base:'', Primary:'primary', Dark:'dark'}
          div.-pr--2
            chi-button(color=type, outline)= val
    .a-col.-w--12.-w-md--6
      .-p--3.-bg--black.-d--flex(style="justify-content: center;")
        each type, val in {Secondary:'secondary', Light:'light'}
          div.-pr--2
            chi-button(color=type, outline)= val
  :code(lang='html')
    <chi-button outline>Base</chi-button>
    <chi-button color='primary' outline>Primary</chi-button>
    <chi-button color='dark' outline>Dark</chi-button>
    <chi-button color='secondary' outline>Secondary</chi-button>
    <chi-button color='light' outline>Light</chi-button>

h4 Flat
p.-text
